<TEXT>
a federal jury convicted a colombian drug 
kingpin tuesday of masterminding a massive 1985 airlift of cocaine 
to nevada 
benjamin herrera the socalled black pope of cocaine was 
convicted of conspiracy and importation by us district court 
jurors who deliberated less than two hours before returning the 
verdict 
herrera who faces up to 80 years in prison and fines totaling 1 
million was scheduled to be sentenced may 25 
the conviction has international implications for the cocaine 
trade because federal drug agents consider herrera one of colombias 
most prominent drug lords said tom green chief of the las vegas 
drug task force 
he and brothers gustavo herrera and romero herrera probably 
operate the largest family cocaine operation in colombia green 
said 
herrera was convicted in the january 1985 shipment of 189 pounds 
of cocaine to southern nevada from bolivia the drug had a street 
value of 17 million 
drug enforcement administration agents in florida were alerted to 
the planned deal by a government informant adler barry seal 
who enabled undercover agents to infiltrate the scheme 
the drugs were flown to an airport outside of las vegas and 
several men were arrested while picking the shipment up they were 
later convicted of drug charges in federal court 
herrera was arrested by federal agents in miami in december 1987 
seal was assassinated by gunmen in baton rouge la in february 
1986 while preparing to testify against alleged drug lords in miami 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

