conference sources said the meetings were also expected to try 
and heal the rift between iran and saudi arabia and hopefully talk 
the two islamic powers into resuming diplomatic relations 
saudi arabia severed ties with iran last year to protest alleged 
iranian attempts to instigate shiite moslem supporters to sabotage 
oil and public utility installations in the kingdom 
the sources speaking on condition of anonymity said the 
ministers hope to convince iran and iraq to accept a simultaneous 
release of all prisoners of war a unbrokered ceasefire halted 
eight years of hostilities between iran and iraq on aug 20 but 
peace talks launched five days later have been deadlocked over the 
issue of troop withdrawals 
both countries are members of the islamic conference tehran sent 
a lowranking delegation to the meeting 
conference members mainly arab countries were expected to 
criticize irans efforts to export its fundamentalist revolution to 
neighboring nations the sources said 
the iranian delegation was expected to appeal to the conferences 
foreign ministers to support ayatollah ruhollah khomeinis edict 
urging moslems to kill british writer salman rushdie for allegedly 
blaspheming islam in his novel the satanic verses 
saudi arabia has criticized rushdie and banned his book but 
would not support khomeinis death threat 
arab diplomatic sources have said the saudis will resist irans 
attempts to project khomeini as defender of islam they said 
khomeini was bent on using the rushdie affair to arouse public 
sentiment hoping to improve unfavorable political conditions at 
home 
moslems were offended by a scene in rushdies book where 
prostitutes take their names after prophet mohammeds four wives in 
the novel rushdie also suggests that mohammed wrote the koran the 
holy book of islam rather than receiving it directly from god 
the conference sessions were held behind closed doors and the 
saudis were understood to have argued that khomeinis order only 
portrays moslems as bloodthirsty and precipitates unnecessary rifts 
with the west 
conference sources said the saudis were to offer a compromise 
proposal based on sending conference delegations to western 
countries to request that rushdies book be denounced and banned 
meanwhile the saudi newspaper okaz reported that the conference 
was to discuss collective action to regain the arab sector of 
jerusalem okaz said that islamic conference member nations want the 
sector of jerusalem occupied by israel in 1967 to become capital of 
a palestinian state 
the foreign ministers it said plan to discuss ways to bolster 
the palestinian uprising against israel in the occupied west bank 
and gaza strip 
