fifty years ago wednesday nazi 
troops invaded czechoslovakia in what one historian says was an 
unavoidable consequence of the wests abandonment of the nation and 
adolf hitlers plan to conquer europe 
in september 1938 czechoslovakias allies britain and france 
bowed to german pressure and agreed to hitlers annexation of 
czechoslovakias germanspeaking sudetenland region nearly 
onethird of the nations territory 
any western hopes that appeasement would dissuade hitler from 
allout war on eastern europe ended germany invaded the rest of 
czechoslovakia on march 15 1939 
