a federal judge approved the settlement of the 
governments civil racketeering case against the teamsters on 
tuesday saying it meant the unions leadership is pledged to keep 
it free from the influence of organized crime 
us district judge david n edelstein signed the agreement 
reached just before a trial of the governments lawsuit was to begin 
monday noting that the teamsters union has had a long and sordid 
career of corruption and involvement with criminal elements 
but in agreeing to the settlement which will implement sweeping 
reforms including the direct election of the unions top leadership 
teamster officials have today done their members a great 
service edelstein said 
however teamsters president william j mccarthy one of the 
individual defendants in the case was less enthusiastic in his 
comments 
while i reluctantly accept the terms of the consent order i 
believe it is not the vindication and exoneration teamsters 
deserve mccarthy said in a statement issued by the union the 
fact is this suit should never have been filed in the first place 
under the tentative agreement which the government says will 
wrest the nations largest trade union from mafia domination three 
courtappointed watchdogs will oversee the teamsters union for three 
years 
edelstein received the settlement monday afternoon but delayed 
approving it to clarify apparent ambiguities on matters of serious 
importance 
the main change made at edlesteins request was that the 
government and the teamsters agree on two names to submit to the 
judge for each of the watchdog positions so that six names instead 
of three will be offered for the three posts 
the settlement announced just hours before the start of the 
trial on a federal civil racketeering lawsuit to oust the unions 
allegedly mobinfluenced executive board was reached early monday 
after roundtheclock weekend negotiations 
the lawsuit filed last june claimed the teamsters leadership 
had been dominated by organized crime which deprived union members 
of their rights through racketeering and a campaign of fear that 
included 20 murders dozens of bombings and other violence 
most of the 26 reputed mobsters originally named as defendants in 
the case were dismissed when they either agreed or were ordered to 
drop any involvement with the teamsters five including convicted 
colombo crime family boss carmine junior persico have been 
severed from the case and are to be tried later 
for the first time in teamsters history the unions top leaders 
will be elected directly by the membership in secret ballot votes 
beginning in 1991 
currently delegates to the national convention pick the 
executive board members by rollcall vote 
under the settelement the three overseers will be appointed for 
three years by the judge with the joint approval of both sides one 
would investigate and prosecute alleged union corruption another 
would administer disciplinary action and the third would oversee 
elections 
after the 1991 union elections are certified the three overseers 
will be replaced by an independent review board empowered to 
investigate and remedy allegations of corruption 
