just coolin atlantic levert 
 
levert describes side 1 of just coolin as a conceptual 
funk suite and the term is unintentionally apt the five songs 
will send most listeners into a conceptual funk that will have them 
secondguessing their recordbuying habits 
in an attempt to attract a younger audience levert has made 
music for the curbside with a backbeat guaranteed to drown out all 
conversation and even honking cars the problem is it sounds like 
the same backbeat on all five songs 
monotonous is not a strong enough word the music lacks the humor 
or grit of the best rap and the street dialogue between cuts is 
lame 
side 2 sees levert revert to the ballads that helped make their 
first two albums big sellers the tunes are in the marvin gaye 
tradition the late singer is even mentioned in lets get 
romantic but again theres no variety in the tempos and the 
songs arent good enough to justify the sleepinducing pace the 
slow side is better than side 1 but so is tiffany 
the best strategy for levert at this point would be to find some 
stronger material put out another album quickly and announce they 
were just foolin about just coolin refunds would be nice too 
by steven wine associated press writer 
</TEXT>
