i wanna have some fun jive samantha fox 
 
on the cover of this her third album we find miss fox pretty 
much clothed which must mean the former british pinup queen is 
getting serious about this music thing what she isnt getting is 
much better 
oh all right most of this is harmless enough i guess she has 
a serviceable if unspectacular voice and she has an army of 
producers behind her creating synthopop dance music the likes of 
which donna summer did an awful lot better 10 years ago 
but theres one track in this morass that sinks below the others 
a blasphemous synthedup ruination of the dusty springfield classic 
i only want to be with you whoever is responsible should be 
forced to listen to the original or to southside johnnys soulful 
remake repeatedly while doing some prison time somewhere gaaaaak 
