<TEXT>
after nearly 12 hours of negotiations 
common market countries on tuesday tentatively adopted eecwide 
television broadcast rules designed to stem the flood of us shows 
and encourage european productions 
at a european economic community trade ministers meeting 
belgium denmark and west germany voted against the legislation but 
could not block it under eec voting rules 
the eec law stipulates an unspecified majority of televison 
programs excluding news and sports casts must be of european 
origin to be shown throughout the 12nation community 
this applies to both eec and noneec broadcasters the eec law 
also sets out minimum standards of morality and regulates the 
frequency and duration of commercial breaks 
jean dondelinger the eec commissioner for audiovisual affairs 
welcomed the accord we now have across the community the same 
legislation on television broadcasting he said 
his draft law included a minimum 60 percent european content 
clause 
this was rejected in talks among the eec states that revealed a 
rift between northern and southern states as to how far the 
community must discriminate in favor of european content the eecs 
southern nations favored stricter europeancontent rules in 
television 
officials said the law is designed to limit the number of 
relatively cheap american television productions from west european 
television screens and to encourage more european programming 
it is estimated that 70 percent of television programs shown in 
europe are of noneec origin the overwhelming majority of them 
american 
tuesdays agreement will be completed april 13 they said 
the eec law also aims to encourage local production of programs 
in eec nations with a weak production capacity or which have 
language restraints it also forces broadcasters to fix a minimum 10 
percent of broadcast time for european programs by independent 
producers 
belgium voted against the plan saying it lacked adequate 
protection for its dutch and frenchspeaking broadcast industries 
denmarks opposition arose from a belief the eec commission lacks 
the ability to monitor compliance with the legislation 
in voting against the legislation west germany argued the 11 
west german states not the bonn government are responsible for 
broadcasting 
also officials said bonn wanted the eec legislation to consider 
east bloc television productions as european which is not the 
case under the eec law 
the eec plan is in line with a draft broadcasting convention of 
the 22nation council of europe a cultural and political 
organization based in strasbourg france the council of europe 
which is a separate body from the eec is to finalize its convention 
later this week 
